source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тимур!..

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: С этой забавной девочкой хлебнешь горя, – снова повторила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я ей говорю «а», она мне «бэ»!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Напрасно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Говорила, я ее выругала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Что значит «спокойно»? – утирая платком запыленные губы, спросила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут Георгий переменил голос и, подражая хору, пропел: – Старик, спокойно… спокойно!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: О, горе мне… о, горе!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он бывший партизан, и он немного… не в себе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я играю старика инвалида, – не переставая возиться у мотоцикла, ответил Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Вы кого в вашей опере играете? – присаживаясь на траву, спросила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Подождите, – соскакивая, сказал Георгий, – маленькая авария.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Прямо! – предостерегающе кричала Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Это наш завод! – прокричал Ольге Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Здесь дорога лучше, – отвечал Георгий, – здесь дорога веселая.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Вы не туда повернули, – крикнула Ольга, – нам надо направо!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я… и так, без цветов, с вами поеду.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Цветов не надо! – сама испугавшись своего поступка, виновато ответила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но мне думается, что так, как вы, не поступают люди… даже самой железобетонной специальности.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Вы хорошо играете, поете, глаза у вас прямые, светлые.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Послушайте! – огорченно сказал он.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга покраснела, растерялась и… бросила его на дорогу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хотел соврать, да не вышло.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну, верно, – согласился Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Неправда! – не поверила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я ехал, – объяснил ей Георгий, – смотрю, вы идете.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Беда! – прокричал он обернувшись.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Беда, Женя!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, отряхивая слипшиеся волосы, отплевываясь и отфыркиваясь, длинными саженками он поплыл на другой берег.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Прыгнули!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, прыгнули?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ты не плачь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И тебя я тоже знаю, – обернулась она к Тане.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А вон Тимур! – сбросив платье, показала она на усыпанный ребятами противоположный берег.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я тебя узнала сразу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Девочка, ты меня узнала? – как всегда быстро и сквозь зубы, спросила она у Жени.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здесь они наткнулись на Нюрку.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот погодите, приедет папа…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, всплеснув руками, Женя с отчаянием добавила: – Ну, сестра, сестра и сестра!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Пусть он не жалеет, – покраснев, пробормотала Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Меня зовут Таней, и я тоже из его команды.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я приплыла от Тимура.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Здравствуй, – сказала ей высокая темноглазая девочка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она обернулась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Их тянули за руки, за ноги, разнимали…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – На и тебе тоже! – обозлился Фигура и ударил Алешку наотмашь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это хорошо ли?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну, – угрожающе спросил Фигура, – а ты кто – капитан, что ли?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – У него брат – матрос, – хмуро объяснил бритоголовый Алешка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Фигура плюнул.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И из-за двери глухо, едва слышно донеслось:

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну что? – подходя к двери и прикладывая ко рту ладонь, закричал Фигура.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Чую я, что будет сегодня у нас позывной сигнал по форме номер один общий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Коля, – подбадривающе буркнул он, – ты не робей.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Бей хоть сто раз, – зажмурившись и вновь открывая глаза, сказал Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Нет, будет! – крикнул Фигура и ударил Гейку по щеке.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Этого не будет, – ровно ответил Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но… мы люди добрые.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – За такие ультиматумы надо бы вам набить шею, – подходя к Гейке, сказал Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – На, возьми, – протягивая бумагу, сказал Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ответ на письмо давайте, – холодно повторил Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Давай поговорим, – предложил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Квакин улыбался, Фигура хмурился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ответ на письмо давайте, – твердо сказал Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это все на двоих-то? – надменно спросил Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Не ходи, – дергая за руку Гейку, прошептал Коля.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А заходите справа! – закричал из-за ограды Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Подавай наверх Михаила Квакина! – приказал Гейка высунувшемуся сверху мальчишке.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Труби, Николай, вот и ограда.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Скажет сто слов, а можно бы четыре.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Этакий балабон! – покачал головой Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Гоп-гоп, до свиданья!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну ладно, вы туда, а я сюда.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Идешь по делу – надел бы сапоги, ботинки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Гейка, дурак!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Экий ты сегодня важный!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Коля, дай-ка я дудану в трубу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вам свое, а у меня свое дело.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Так надо, и ты ничего не понимаешь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Меня Тимур послал для связи, – затараторил Симаков.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Похитил байковое одеяло? – растерялся старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да, представьте! – заглядывая старику за спину и начиная волноваться, продолжал джентльмен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Что?! – изумился старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Этот некий мальчик – мой племянник.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Да, приходится, – ответил старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – На этой даче живу я, – ответил старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: На замке, в больнице.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да, да!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты, дорогой мой, не трудись! – прибавляя ходу и не переставая оборачиваться, продолжала она.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я, батюшка, потом. – подхватывая бидон и поспешно удаляясь, заговорила молочница.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Лишнего мне не надо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: По рубль сорок – всего два восемьдесят.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Как у людей, – ответила ему молочница.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Платить сколько? – засовывая руку в карман широченных штанов, спросил старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Этакой саблей простого человека и до смерти напугать можно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Посуда на столе, – коротко ответил старик и воткнул саблю клинком в землю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Две кружки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я, батюшка, говорю, молочка не надо ли?– оробев и попятившись, предложила молочница.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Две кружки! – раздался в ответ басистый голос.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Молока не надо ли, молока?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Хорошо, – согласился Фигура.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Мне, конечно, на Тимкины знаки наплевать, и Тимку я всегда бить буду…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Так вот… – с досадой пробормотал Квакин, тыкая пальцем в стену.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, я.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: На том и порешили.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ты что там мычишь, Фигура?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А что к чему – неизвестно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: То отец, то брат, то дядя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Вот дурак – заладил! – рассердился Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Он не заплачет, – сказал бритоголовый, – у него брат – матрос.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – А, тогда так бы и говорили! – с досадой сказал Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бить будут, – опять объяснил бритоголовый Алешка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – То есть в каком смысле свободу? – опять переспросил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А какой дальше слог, какие запятые!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Читаю дальше.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – А, так бы и писали! – сказал Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бить будут, – объяснил стоявший рядом с Фигурой бритоголовый мальчуган Алешка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это что такое, я не знаю, – насмешливо объявил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Эк они завернули: «гнуснопрославленный»!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это тебе, – с удовлетворением объяснил Квакин Фигуре.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я, братцы, право, ничего не понимаю!..

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это что же такое? – переворачивая пакет и оглядывая разинувших рты ребят, спросил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сроку на размышление вам двадцать четыре часа дадено.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Возьми пакет, – протягивая ультиматум, сказал Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Эге, Гейка, здорово!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я тут, – залезая на ограду, отозвался Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Брось карты, тут к тебе какая-то церемония пришла!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Мишка! – оборачиваясь, заорал он.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Нет, не улетай так далеко… как твой папа.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ой, не надо! – подхватывая и сжимая дочурку, воскликнула ее мать.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Далеко-далеко, как папа.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Мама, – попросила она, – сделай мне качели, и я буду летать туда-сюда, туда-сюда.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Нет, – ответил летчик-капитан, – нашими и вашими товарищами.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вами?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Кем? – радостно и растерянно воскликнула женщина.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ни в Крым, ни на Кавказ, ни на курорт, ни в санаторий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Это ко мне, – сказала женщина.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я козу искала, – уныло ответила Нюрка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Украли!– горестно пожаловалась бабка молочнице.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А какая была коза!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, голубь, а не коза.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Голубь!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – А ты, бабушка, не видишь – это я работаю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Нюрка, – спросила ее бабка, – ты не видала, кто к нам сейчас во двор заскакивал?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Папа!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да… мучительница! – со слезами ответила Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это-то я знаю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Очень простых.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В белых костюмах.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот смотри!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Евгения!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Этот мальчишка – хулиган, а ты глупа, – холодно выговаривала, стараясь казаться спокойной, Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я тебе знакомых не выбираю, – с отчаянием защищалась Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Каких?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну вот, – огорченно ответил Тимур, – и мой дядя тебя тоже!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Постой, причешись.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Коля Колокольчиков не явился, и провода все еще исправлены не были.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, наконец, не зная, что и думать, она стала стучать в окно соседке.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вышла ошибка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Рассвело.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Нет?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но она не могла.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она вздрагивала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, когда папа уезжал, он мне велел…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Но, Оля, ты ничего, ничего не понимаешь! – с отчаянием воскликнула Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я твоя сестра… Я старше.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Евгения! – тяжело дыша, со слезами в голосе сказала Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но, Оля, – пробормотала Женя, – что с тобою?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я запрещаю тебе подходить к этому мальчишке, – твердо повторила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Окрик резкий и даже гневный заставил их обернуться.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Да, – ответил Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И только для того, чтобы хоть что-нибудь сказать, она спросила:

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А разве Гейка добрый?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И если тебе случится, то сделай ей, Женя, что-нибудь хорошее.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но его уже нет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Вот! – сказал Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Да! – с волнением и гордостью ответила Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он командир.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я – Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Тише, Женя! – громко сказал он.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Уходите!..

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кто вы такие? – отступая от окна, в страхе спросила Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сейчас примчатся… люди, и они тебя поколотят.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Оставь штурвальное колесо и беги прочь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Сумасшедшая девчонка! – резко и почти испуганно прокричал тот же голос.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это я – Женя!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Это не осел, – пробормотала озадаченная Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Лево руля на борт! – громко скомандовала Женя и крепче налегла на тяжелое колесо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ей показалось, что это ее корабль-сарай медленно и спокойно по волнам разворачивается.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В небе играли голуби.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Возле дырявой замшелой крыши торчало большое, похожее на штурвальное, колесо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Нет, тебе! – хватая пустое ведро, уже с крыльца откликнулась Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это вступил он.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну и положу, – обиделась Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Положи инструмент на место! –вскакивая, крикнула Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А я ему говорю: «Бэ-э!»

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А он тогда говорит.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: «Нет, – говорю я ему, – она уже учится по железобетонной специальности».

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – «Очень, – говорит он, – твоя сестра хорошо играет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Женька, не мешай и инструмент не трогай! – невольно прислушиваясь, повторила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – «А твою сестру, – доставая аккордеон, продолжала Женя, – кажется, зовут Ольгой?»

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я говорю: «Женя…»

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Знаешь, Оля!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А у тебя – вот… вот… и вот…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Глупая! – обнимая ее, целуя и легонько отталкивая, сказала Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот, посмотри, срежешься!..

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Олечка, не ходи на инженера, ходи на доктора, – заговорила Женя, подсовывая Ольге настольное зеркало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Инженер должен быть – вот… вот… и вот…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя, – недовольно спросила Ольга, – откуда у тебя на плече царапина?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Стой, сумасшедшая собака! – крикнул Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И наконец низкий баритон запел.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Потом этакое тра-ля-ля!..

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И точно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ага, Рита! Мы с тобой попались.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ты смотри! Я все замечаю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И ты оставил ее утром одну… в квартире?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты, друг мой, болен, и тебя надо отправить в сумасшедший.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот и врешь! – рассердился старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: «Девочка, когда будешь уходить, захлопни крепче дверь», – насмешливо прочел старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Одна знакомая девочка, – неохотно ответил мальчуган.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вперед! Молнией!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это не «три – стоп», «три – стоп».

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это какой-то болван кладет колесом десять ударов кряду.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Еще и еще кто-то.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да нет!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Слушай… Я не пойму.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: С какой же это, позвольте, целью? – начал было спрашивать удивленный джентльмен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ты ночью по веревке из окна лазил, – не поворачивая головы, хладнокровно ляпнула Татьянка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Она врет, бессовестная! – бросая на Татьянку сердитый взгляд, воскликнул оскорбленный Коля.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пожилой джентльмен, доктор Ф. Г. Колокольчиков, сидел в своем саду и чинил стенные часы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это ты-то одинокая и беззащитная? – недоверчиво спросила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Что ж, папа! – скорбно, с пафосом воскликнула Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Кого? – И Ольга недоуменно подняла покрытое мыльной пеной лицо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Отстань! И на что это тебе Тимур дался?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А если не царь, не злой и не из средней, тогда кто?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Отстань! – с досадой ответила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Нету, – ответила Ольга и подставила голову под умывальник.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Оля, бог есть?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А мне папа велел…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И вечно нелепые у тебя шутки…

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Да… но я беспокоилась, – с отчаянием заговорила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Оля! – горестно воскликнула тогда Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ниже стояла подпись: «Тимур».

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В этой записке крупно синим карандашом было написано: «Девочка, никого дома не бойся.»

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Мое, – шепотом ответила Женя, робко оглядываясь в сторону террасы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – А это чье? Не твое? – И девчонка показала ей ключ от московской квартиры.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Нет, – не поняла Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Такой, знаешь ли, странный случай, такое необычайное приключение!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну, ругайся, – покорно согласилась Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Буду! – не сводя глаз с сестры, ответила Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Оля, ты ругаться не будешь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Оля, здравствуй! – останавливаясь на верхней ступеньке и пытаясь улыбнуться, сказала Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Скверно! Был бы папа, он бы понял.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Упало на пепельницу настольное зеркало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Справа, возле кожаных автомобильных краг, лежал старый, ободранный револьвер.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тимур? Кто такой Тимур?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дура!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да! – Она показала собаке язык.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты лови разбойников и шпионов, а я… человек.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Очень странно, – чуть не плача, заговорила она.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну вот! Ты лежишь? И лежи… Очень хорошая собачка… такая с виду умная, симпатичная.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я не вор! Я у вас ничего не взяла.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ты, глупая! – испуганно растопыривая пальцы, закричала Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя огляделась: уже смеркалось, а людей вокруг видно не было.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Скажи, дорогая, пожалуйста, – закричала ей Женя, – как мне пройти отсюда на почту?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это был местный житель, доктор Ф. Г. Колокольчиков.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здешний, – нехотя ответил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это еще что за пропагандист выискался? Здешний?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Не так ли?
