sentence: Он из компании хулигана Квакина.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: К ней привязался какой-то мальчишка, зовут Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Очень забавная девочка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я слаб.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я стар.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Не спи, моя страна!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ползут в тиши враги.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я третью ночь не сплю в глухом дозоре.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За тучами опять померкнула луна.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Красноармейцы же молодые – смеются, после караула в волейбол играют.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он стар, но он осторожен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он живет близ границы, и ему все кажется, что враги нас перехитрят и обманут.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Почему у вас грим такой суровый и страшный?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вдруг мотор заглох, и они остановились.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Давайте только прямо домой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Почти не уменьшая хода, машина круто развернулась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Откашливаясь, она села на ступеньку, отдышалась, взяла лейку и пошла в огород.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бабка набрала в подол огурцов и собиралась идти во двор.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сима Симаков тихонько постучал по доскам забора.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бабка насторожилась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тогда Сима поднял палку и начал ею шевелить ветви яблони.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Папа, приезжай скорей!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Мне, твоей Женьке, очень трудно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А теперь возьми и читай.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга положила на стол полученную ночью телеграмму и вышла.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы бы лучше послушали, как она прекрасно ругается.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я уже обо всем пишу папе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ты знаешь, что у меня слово бывает твердое?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сестры стояли на террасе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Что ты делаешь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты сегодня очень лохматый.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Увидав Тимура, она не испугалась и даже не удивилась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Не знаю за что, но моя сестра тебя очень ненавидит.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Уже поднималось солнце.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она хотела объяснить, оправдаться.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тебе тринадцать, мне восемнадцать.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Неподалеку стояла Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя дотронулась до руки Тимура: она хотела подвести его и познакомить с ним Ольгу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но новый окрик, строгий и холодный, заставил ее от этого отказаться.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Виновато кивнув Тимуру головой и недоуменно пожав плечами, она пошла к Ольге.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я запрещаю тебе разговаривать с этим мальчишкой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он сын моряка, матроса.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она молчала, наклонив голову.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это дача лейтенанта Павлова, которого недавно убили на границе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И из этого дома человек ушел в Красную Армию.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Значит, и ты находишься под нашей охраной и защитой тоже.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Они остановились перед воротами другой дачи.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И здесь на заборе была начерчена звезда.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но прямые светлые лучи ее были обведены широкой черной каймой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты объясни мне проще: что все это значит?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Мы с тобой знакомы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Никто тебя не тронет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кричать не надо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Все обернулись и расступились.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В то же мгновение в просвете мелькнула еще одна тень.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, очутившись прижатой к углу, Женя вскрикнула.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но плечо к плечу, плотной стеной ребята молча шли на Женю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я вас сюда не звала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это наш сад.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя бросила трубку, но было уже поздно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Какой осел обрывает провода и подает сигналы, глупые и непонятные?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она сняла трубку.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ей стало не по себе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Этого Женя не ожидала; она думала, что этот телефон просто игрушка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пыльной ладонью Женя вытерла лоб, и вдруг на стене задребезжал звонок телефона.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бой был окончен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это разгромленная вражья эскадра шла ко дну.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И это, конечно, не солнце зашло за тучу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но вот острые прямые лучи прожектора поблекли, погасли.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Прорвавшись через щели крыши, узкие прямые лучи солнца упали ей на лицо и платье.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ветер зашумел и погнал зеленые волны.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тугие веревочные провода задрожали, загудели.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она повернула штурвальное колесо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ей стало весело.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она же сама будет капитаном.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, если бы еще мне было лет сорок или хотя бы тридцать.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Перед ней, как волны моря, колыхалась листва густых садов.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Все было тихо, и он просунул голову в отверстие – послушать, что делается внутри сада.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но эта работа была ей не под силу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя заглянула через щель.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: От канавы отделилось трое.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Три года тому назад я сюда ездил собирать грибы и землянику.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Над колесом висел самодельный телефон.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, не успев крикнуть, он отлетел от забора.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Размахивая обожженными руками, Сима помчался к воротам, откуда уже выбегала закончившая свою работу четверка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут же стоял перевернутый фанерный ящик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Смотри молчи!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Как тяжелый снаряд, прогудела встречная грузовая машина.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В углу лежала покрытая мешковиной охапка соломы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А то я не посмотрю, что ты за меня заступался.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Обеспокоенный, он подпрыгнул, схватился за край забора и осторожно стал подтягиваться.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она подтащила к окну трухлявую лестницу и, взобравшись по ней, спрыгнула на пол чердака.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И неожиданно он пронзительно свистнул.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Выскочила из стада и затявкала, пытаясь догнать их, собака.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя обошла сарай, через дырявую крышу которого разбегались во все стороны тонкие веревочные провода.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но тотчас же рот его был зажат широкой ладонью Гейки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сима Симаков опять заглянул в щель, но бабки теперь он не увидел.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Взлетев кверху ногами, парашютист перевернулся.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Чьи-то руки подхватили его за плечи, за ноги и уволокли прочь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Опять поворот, и они промчались через шумливую тенистую рощу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я тебе не грузовик, не конь и не трактор.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Свист в саду услыхали.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она высыпала огурцы на межу, выдернула большой пук крапивы, подкралась и притаилась у забора.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты мешаешь мне заниматься.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Свист больше не повторился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дорога раздваивалась, но, минуя ту, что сворачивала к поселку, мотоцикл вырвался в поле.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот погоди, приедет папа, он тебе покажет!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Квакин внимательно оглядывался по сторонам.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бабке тотчас же показалось, что кто-то тихонько лезет через забор за яблоками.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хотела я тебе рассказать дальше, а теперь не буду.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Теперь ему показалось, что кусты в углу сада шевельнулись.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она села на кожаную подушку, и мотоцикл полетел вдоль дороги.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я и не вступала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это ты там, дурак, прячешься?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За этим занятием и застала его вернувшаяся из огорода бабка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кто тебе разрешает вступать в разговоры с какими-то дяденьками?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но это были не хозяева.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я вас ничем не обидел.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Негодная девчонка!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Позади, в гуще листвы, вспыхнуло не меньше десятка электрических фонарей.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Во дворе опять остался только один малыш.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя достала аккордеон и перекинула ремень через плечо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, слепя глаза, они стремительно надвигались на растерявшихся налетчиков.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Этого Георгий не ожидал.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она не хочет ли учиться в консерватории?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И еще десяток мальчишек рванулись с тылу и с фланга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В калитку вошла Нюрка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Подходит ко мне сегодня какой-то дяденька.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да у них сила!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Букет был хорош.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А потом дрова покидали и опять ускочили.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты бы лучше сбегала к колодцу за водой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За забор вылетай, ребята!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Уходи, Женя, и не мешай.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Попавшая в засаду шайка в панике метнулась к забору.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он положил ей букет на книгу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут Женя повела глазами, приподняла брови и очень неясно улыбнулась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Луна совсем спряталась за тучи.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пробовали они добиться ответа у малыша, однако добились немногого.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он и колючий и острый.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пленных не бить!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга отрицательно качнула головой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, погляди: какой из тебя инженер?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Где Гейка?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это кто же тут без меня работает?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот так и получилось.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Веди всех на место.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Садитесь, я подвезу вас на машине.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Теперь вздрагивающая бечевка ослабла – должно быть, где-то лопнула.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А если кто не пойдет?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я все утро по лесу да по оврагам сама скакала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тогда, удивленный и рассерженный, он схватил трубку телефона.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хватайте за руки, за ноги и тащите с почетом, как икону богородицы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это я в гриме готовился к репетиции.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Часом раньше, чем все это случилось, Ольга сидела за столом.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хулиганить мастера, а отвечать боитесь!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За воротами послышался шум машины, а по дорожке от калитки шли два летчика-командира.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Перед нею лежал учебник физики.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пленников подвели к пустой будке на краю базарной площади.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ведь хромой старик у калитки – это был я.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вошла Женя и достала пузырек с йодом.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут их одного за другим протолкнули за дверь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы хотели повидать вашу маму?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Что ты мне рвешь штаны и куда ты меня тянешь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Все готово.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я должен перед вами извиниться за то, что напугал вас утром.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Мальчуган зажал его в руке, замотал бечевку на гвоздь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Последнего пленника втолкнули в будку, задвинули засов и просунули в пробой тяжелый замок.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ваша мать сегодня поездом выезжает к вам из Иркутска.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он сейчас петь будет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты смешон.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы стояли и ожидали меня нарочно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сверху из комнаты послышалось откашливание.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты никому не страшен и не нужен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: До Иркутска она была доставлена на специальном самолете.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ничего, он сегодня добрый.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ожидая, что его будут бить, ничего не понимая, Квакин стоял, опустив голову.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дай, думаю, подожду и подвезу, если по дороге.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пристукивая деревяшкой, старик пошел вверх по лестнице.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Возьми вот этот ключ и отопри часовню, где сидит твой друг Фигура.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Игра была в самом разгаре, когда за оградой раздался резкий звук сигнальной трубы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Похоже было на то, что старик улыбнулся.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Квакин не уходил.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Они поздоровались.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну хорошо, что револьвер был заряжен холостыми.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Или посади меня вместе с ними.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это снаружи у стены стояли посланцы от команды Тимура.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А если бы в нем были патроны боевые?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ни им с тобою, ни тебе с ними больше делать нечего.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И там, где крутая тропка пересекала дорогу, ее встретил стоявший возле мотоцикла Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Эта дрянь разбила зеркало, расколотила пепельницу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Под свист, шум и улюлюканье, спрятав голову в плечи, Квакин медленно пошел прочь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А это еще что с тобой за хлюпик?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А теперь я ее знаю.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Отойдя десяток шагов, он остановился и выпрямился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Читая книгу, Ольга поднималась в гору.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Не знал.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Бить буду тебя одного.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За ответом приду завтра в такое же время.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Когда я писал, то я не знал.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Один на один, до смерти!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Гейка и Коля попали в засаду!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ее без меня задержала собака.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И, отпрыгнув, он скрылся в темноте.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вероятно, ругательство или что-нибудь в этом смысле.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В одной руке он держал записку, другой сжимал старый, ободранный револьвер.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: У тебя что?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но не успели девчонки вынырнуть, как вслед за ними бултыхнулся кто-то четвертый.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: К колену его левой ноги ремнями была пристегнута грубая деревяшка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Рядом на станции заревел гудок.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это такое международное слово.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Широченные штаны – в заплатках.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Прибыл дачный поезд.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И они разом бросились в воду.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: К нему подошел седой лохматый старик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: С него сходили пассажиры, и Тимур заторопился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Отрасти, Алеша, волосы, а то тебе солнце напекло затылок.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Симаков и твоя пятерка, у тебя что?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Холщовая рубаха его была бедна.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Очень уж она была смешная, эта маленькая, загорелая, похожая на цыганку Нюрка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: На нем были легкие черные брюки и темно-синяя безрукавка с вышитой красной звездой.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дом номер тридцать восемь по Малой Петраковской.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Слушай, это ты в тот сад лазил, где живет девчонка, у которой отца убили?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: До свиданья!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А вот посмотрим!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя и Таня переглянулись.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ага, проверим!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хорошо, работайте!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А что ты мне пальцем на чертей тычешь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Какой позывной?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Гром и стук раздался по площади.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Девочки, давайте в воду прыгнем!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это тревога?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Шарахнулись и остановились идущие с поезда прохожие.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Утром молочница не застала дома троих постоянных покупателей.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здесь с ними столкнулся широкоплечий, крепкий мальчуган Гейка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Стук и вой повторился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты один раз сидела на грядке и плакала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Следом подскочил Василий Ладыгин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Загорелись огни в окнах соседних дач.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она ходила долго без толку и наконец остановилась возле дачи, где жил Тимур.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Они вышли из воды и забрались на крутой берег, левей песчаного пляжа.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это, кажется, по форме номер один позывной сигнал общий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здесь сидят люди, которые трусливо по ночам обирают сады мирных жителей.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Они перепрыгнули через забор, нырнули в дыру ограды парка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Поздняя ночь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За забором она услышала густой приятный голос: кто-то негромко пел.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но тут со стороны курятника раздался лязг и звон.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И черно-красной звезды на воротах не видно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга совсем не злая, у нее такой характер.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: То есть как на трубе?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но она тут.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Значит, хозяева были дома и здесь можно было ожидать удачи.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дрожь пронизала тело от головы до пяток.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сад того дома, где живет маленькая девочка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: У тебя сестра, наверное, очень злая?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дух захватило у Коли Колокольчикова при этих наглых словах бессовестной Татьянки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: С ветвистого дерева спустились веревки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Экий ты, отец мой, с виду серьезный!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кинет да посвистит, кинет да еще свистнет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вслед за ними по шершавому стволу соскользнул мальчик.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он жалеет, что тебе из-за него от сестры попало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А в спальню к нам вчера какой-то хулиган кидал камнем.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он кладет доску, садится и пробует, прочны ли они, эти новые качели.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты что ж это, саблей траву косишь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: У тебя под подушкой есть фонарь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Толстый сук чуть поскрипывает, листва шуршит и вздрагивает.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Неожиданно кто-то обнял ее за плечи.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Три раза я давал ей откусить по два раза.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вспорхнула и пискнула потревоженная птица.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А саблю лучше брось.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Например, вчера ты съел четыре порции мороженого, а с младшей сестрой не поделился.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Уже поздно.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя купалась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тебе же душевного благородства как раз не хватает.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Спит давно Ольга, спит Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
